ational Rosalie Wolf Award, National Committee for Prevention of Elder Abuse<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.preventelderabuse.org/about/award.html|title=Rosalie Wolf Award Recipients|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=24 January 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n!Before 2012\n|-\n|'''2011''' Maxwell A. Pollack Award for Productive Aging, Gerontological Society of America<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2011-08/tgso-dwg080211.php|title=Dong wins GSA's 2011 Maxwell A. Pollack Award for Productive Aging|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=24 January 2017}}</ref>\n'''2010''' Physician Advocacy Merit Award, Institute of Medicine as Profession<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://imapny.org/physician-advocacy/2010-physician-advocacy-conference/|title=2010 Physician Advocacy Conference|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=24 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''2009''' Central Society for Clinical Research Award<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=tegagcxzSb8C&pg=PA212&lpg=PA212&dq=Central+Society+for+Clinical+Research+Award,+xinqi#v=onepage&q=Central%20Society%20for%20Clinical%20Research%20Award%2C%20xinqi&f=false|title=Central Society for Clinical Research Award|date=2011-09-12|website=|publisher=|access-date=24 January 2017|isbn=9780309211543|last1=Medicine|first1=Institute of|last2=Health|first2=Board on Global|last3=Prevention|first3=Forum on Global Violence}}</ref>\n\n'''2008''' Paul B. Beeson Physician Faculty Award in Aging<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nationalacademies.org/hmd/~/media/708DF1945025402DAE8990F7E580331E.ashx|title=Planning Committee Biographies|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=24 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n'''2006''' Nobuo Maeda International Aging and Public Health Research Award, American Public Health Association<ref name=\":1\" />\n|}\n\n== Current grants ==\n* New Jersey Population Health Cohort Study: [https://www.rwjf.org/en/how-we-work/grants-explorer.html#k=population%20health%20cohort%20study&location=NJ&start=2019 76850, Robert Wood Johnson Foundation] \n*New Jersey Minority Aging Collaborative: R24AG063729<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://projectreporter.nih.gov/project_info_description.cfm?aid=9793350&icde=49661381&ddparam=&ddvalue=&ddsub=&cr=2&csb=FY&cs=DESC&pball=|title=Project Information - NIH RePORTER - NIH Research Portfolio Online Reporting Tools Expenditures and Results|website=projectreporter.nih.gov|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n*Asian Resource Centers for Minority Aging Research (RCMAR): P30AG059304<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://projectreporter.nih.gov/project_info_description.cfm?aid=9776418&icde=49661562&ddparam=&ddvalue=&ddsub=&cr=5&csb=default&cs=ASC&pball=|title=Project Information - NIH RePORTER - NIH Research Portfolio Online Reporting Tools Expenditures and Results|website=projectreporter.nih.gov|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n* National Institute on Nursing Research: R01NR 014846_A1\n* National Institute of Aging/NINR/NIMH: R01AG042318\n* National Institute of Minority Health and Health Disparity: R01MD006173\n* National Cancer Institute: R01CA163830, P20CA165592\n* National Institute on Mental Health: R34 MH 100393A1, R34 MH 100443A1\n* Administration on Aging/ACL: 09EJIG0005-01-00:\n* China Beijing Science and Technology\n* National Opinion Research Center (NORC)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dong, XinQi}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Rush University faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Chicago alumni]]\n[[Category:Rush Medical College alumni]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:21st-century Chinese physicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American physicians]]\n[[Category:Rutgers University faculty]]\n[[Category:Physicians from Jiangsu]]\n[[Category:Scientists from Nanjing]]\n[[Category:American scientists of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:Chinese emigrants to the United States]]\n", "name_user": "JennyNoon", "label": "safe", "comment": "Updated descr